<head>RAIN HAT</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">雨具</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">蓋</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>HAT one WEARS FOR PROTECTION AGAINST RAIN.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. Lì 笠 refers to a large bamboo or reed hat used as protection against rain (and sun).</p>
<p>2. Dēng 簦 refers to a kind of lì 笠 with a handle attached to it.</p>
<p>3. Sǎn 傘 refers to a square dēng 簦, and from Three Kingdom times onwards these could be opened and closed and developed into the predecessor of the modern umbrella.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>笠</p>
